    "When the prompt in the new chat does not give the same categories, we re-write the prompt in order for new categorizations to be explicitly included.",
    "Then we increase the number of bios we give the model to test if the categories are being detected correctly.",
    "After a few more iterations of this process, we settled on the following final prompt: Prompt: If the definition of lifestyle is all things related to how a person or a group of people live, including but not limited to aspects of family, identity, relationship status, occupation, animals/pets, belonging/place, military, religion, sports entertainment, fitness, recreation, education, consumption, pronouns, political issue, and advocacy/activism, then identify lifestyle-related words in the Twitter bio.",
    "Format the output into a table.",
    "The Twitter bio is: ***INSERT TWITTER BIO HERE*** After running that prompt with the rest of the bios, we added the words and categories to the existing dataset."
